The President may, by statutory instrument, make regulations—
(a) prescribing the occasions upon which, the persons by whom and the manner in which the National Anthem may be sung;
prescribing the occasions upon which, the persons by whom and the manner in which the National Anthem may be sung;
(b) prohibiting, controlling or restricting the use of the National Anthem;
prohibiting, controlling or restricting the use of the National Anthem;
(c) constituting offences in relation to any of the matters referred to in the foregoing paragraphs and prescribing penalties in respect thereof.
